wild in about a year.'

The life expectancy of a dormouse is five years and their diet consists of fruit, berries, insects and flowers.

The
UK dormouse population has dropped by more than 70 per cent over the 
last 40 years due to the declining amount of hedgerows, which are their 
natural habitat.

It is thought there are about 45,000 dormice left in the country.

This
year’s poor weather is thought to have affected their population 
drastically as their food sources dwindle in wet conditions.

